# Compiling shine under ubuntu

Shine requires Java, scala and play.

1) Install Java from Oracle or other source

2) Install scala with
  sudo apt-get install scala

3) Download minimal activator from
https://playframework.com/download
unzip and run ./activator to get basic initialization. Add the activator-folder to the path
Alternatively download the full activator and use that.
Alternatively read https://gist.github.com/patarkf/ab2c976b6f89edf90f63

4) Go to the shine sub-folder and run
  activator play
(takes a while the first time, unless the full activator package was installed)
A play-propt should be available. Type
  compile

